Uh, they, they will, uh, the 3011 form will have its own column that shows which categories have ineligible costs and how much that is.

244
00:18:09,647 --> 00:18:16,413
Uh, they all add up at the, at the bottom, and then you essentially remove those costs from the total project budget.

245
00:18:16,980 --> 00:18:20,761
to determine what the cost basis for the reimbursement rate will be.

246
00:18:22,502 --> 00:18:31,324
So that is really the evaluation process that the MSBA will go through.

247
00:18:34,185 --> 00:18:43,647
Looking at some of the bigger cost caps, and really some of the more critical ones,

248
00:18:46,534 --> 00:18:53,379
The most critical one is the building cost funding limit.

249
00:18:53,760 --> 00:19:01,085
So the MSBA will fund up to $605 per square foot of eligible building gross square footage.

250
00:19:02,847 --> 00:19:07,771
We are currently tracking in the six options between 950 and 1,066, I want to say.

251
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:09,432
So you can see just right there,

252
00:19:13,801 --> 00:19:27,426
The MSBA will reimburse $605 per square foot of that, but there's about $400 to $450 per square foot that it will be considered ineligible.

253
00:19:30,107 --> 00:19:38,390
Similar to site work, they reimburse up to $73 per square foot of eligible building gross square footage.

254
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:46,496
Demolition is $42 per square foot of eligible square footage.

255
00:19:47,817 --> 00:19:51,140
Abatement costs are completely ineligible.

256
00:19:52,141 --> 00:19:59,047
So that will be a category that we will always break out once we start to understand the cost of the abatement.

257
00:20:01,049 --> 00:20:03,251
Soft costs caps are capped at 20%.

258
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:12,185
Uh, we have been using a 25% marker, uh, markup from construction costs to total project costs.

259
00:20:12,886 --> 00:20:19,071
Uh, that is, uh, industry standard, uh, and on a project of this size and complexity.

260
00:20:19,091 --> 00:20:24,455
Um, I, I feel that that 25% is, is about where we will land.

261
00:20:25,515 --> 00:20:29,758
Um, but again, the MSBA will, will reimburse up to 20% of that.

262
00:20:33,283 --> 00:20:42,870
They also have caps on what they will reimburse per student on furniture, fixtures, and equipment, as well as the computer equipment and technology.

263
00:20:43,611 --> 00:20:45,532
For FF&E, it's $1,915 per student.

264
00:20:45,592 --> 00:20:47,133
And for technology, it's $1,570 per student.

265
00:20:47,153 --> 00:20:48,334
So combined, that's $3,485 per student.

266
00:21:00,062 --> 00:21:06,266
In a lot of cases, we do find that the FF&E and technology budgets are above these limits.

267
00:21:08,108 --> 00:21:22,157
We're still a little ways out from understanding the full detail of the FF&E and technology, but it is something that we do oftentimes see some costs as being considered ineligible.

268
00:21:24,599 --> 00:21:29,302
Owner's contingency is capped at half of a percent,

269
00:21:30,572 --> 00:21:32,433
And the construction contingency is capped at 1%.

270
00:21:32,993 --> 00:21:47,137
And what this means is when we are in construction and we receive change orders, the MSBA will participate up to these percentages of those reimbursements.

271
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:54,619
So they do participate in some unforeseen change orders that may arise.

272
00:21:55,459 --> 00:21:59,680
But it is a relatively small percentage of those contingencies that we'll carry.

